      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: include provider/model/profile/trigger context in overloaded and rate limit error messages",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nTransient provider failures were still too terse to act on. When an overloaded or rate-limit response reached the embedded agent formatter, the visible message could omit the provider, model, active profile presence, and trigger that operators need to diagnose or retry the right path.\n\n## Solution\n\nThis updates overloaded and rate-limit formatting to append sanitized transient context when available:\n\n- provider/model, for example `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6`\n- `profile=active` when an auth profile was selected\n- `trigger=...`\n\nProvider/model and trigger remain readable. Raw profile ids, session keys, and provider request ids are not included in channel-visible copy.\n\nThe context is threaded through the embedded runner, failover, and payload builders so the same enriched copy is used for chat payloads and lifecycle/error metadata. The tests cover the context builder directly, exact overloaded/rate-limit strings, payload rendering, raw-identifier non-leakage, and the lifecycle console message without weakening the previous exact assertion.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Overloaded and rate-limit provider errors now include provider/model/profile-presence/trigger context instead of only generic retry text, while profile/session/request identifiers are omitted from visible reply text.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw checkout at PR head `45981e01e0f990f83dcb4d6c055d70c8e769663e` on Node 22, executing the production embedded-agent formatter from source.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran `node --import tsx --eval 'import { formatUserFacingAssistantErrorText } from \"./src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers/errors.ts\"; ...'` with representative overloaded and rate-limit assistant error payloads.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Console output from the local OpenClaw command:\n\n```text\noverloaded: The AI service is temporarily overloaded. Please try again in a moment. [anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6, profile=active, trigger=heartbeat]\nrate-limit: ⚠️ API rate limit reached. Please try again later. [openai/gpt-5.4, profile=active, trigger=cron]\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** Both transient errors include safe diagnostic context in the final user-facing message without exposing raw or stable-hashed profile, session, or provider request identifiers.\n- **What was not tested:** Live provider API calls; the proof uses production OpenClaw formatting code with representative provider error payloads.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm test -- src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers.formatassistanterrortext.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/payloads.errors.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.handlers.lifecycle.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 pnpm check:changed --base upstream/main`\n\n## Related issues\n\nCloses #43932\nCloses #51336\nCloses #30262\n",
